Since $p(1) = 3,$ we must have $p(1.5) > 3.$  Also, $p(x)$ is defined and continuous at $x = 1.5,$ so $p(1.5)$ must be a value that is strictly greater than the minimum of $p(x).$

We can see that $p(x)$ is approximately linear near $x = 1,$ so we can approximate $p(x)$ by a line.  The line through $(1,3)$ and $(2,p(2))$ is
